.TH "usb_gadget_deactivate" 9 "usb_gadget_deactivate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_gadget_deactivate \- deactivate function which is not ready to work
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb_gadget_deactivate
.BI "(struct usb_gadget *gadget "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gadget" 12
the peripheral being deactivated
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine may be used during the gadget driver \fBbind\fP call to prevent
the peripheral from ever being visible to the USB host, unless later
\fBusb_gadget_activate\fP is called.  For example, user mode components may
need to be activated before the system can talk to hosts.

Returns zero on success, else negative errno.
